.TH xmerl_eventp 3 "xmerl 2.1.9" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
xmerl_eventp \- Simple event-based processors (front-ends to \fIxmerl_scan\fR).

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Implements processing XML documents in streams for parsing in SAX style.

.PP
Each front-end contains more elaborate settings of \fIxmerl_scan\fR that makes usage of the customization functions.

.SH DATA TYPES
.LP
.B
\fBoption_list() ::\fR
\fB          [{atom(), term()} |\fR
\fB           {atom(), fun(), term()} |\fR
\fB           {atom(), fun(), fun(), term()}].\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Options allow to customize the behaviour of the scanner.  See also the "Customization functions" tutorial.

.PP
<p> Possible options are: </p> <dl> <dt><code>{acc_fun, Fun}</code></dt> <dd>Call back function to accumulate contents of entity.</dd> <dt><code>{continuation_fun, Fun} |

.IP
.nf
       {continuation_fun, Fun, ContinuationState}</code></dt>

.fi

.PP
<dd>Call back function to decide what to do if the scanner runs into EOF

.IP
.nf
before the document is complete.</dd>

.fi

.PP
<dt><code>{event_fun, Fun} |

.IP
.nf
       {event_fun, Fun, EventState}</code></dt>

.fi

.PP
<dd>Call back function to handle scanner events.</dd> <dt><code>{fetch_fun, Fun} |

.IP
.nf
       {fetch_fun, Fun, FetchState}</code></dt>

.fi

.PP
<dd>Call back function to fetch an external resource.</dd> <dt><code>{hook_fun, Fun} |

.IP
.nf
       {hook_fun, Fun, HookState}</code></dt>

.fi

.PP
<dd>Call back function to process the document entities once

.IP
.nf
identified.</dd>

.fi

.PP
<dt><code>{close_fun, Fun}</code></dt> <dd>Called when document has been completely parsed.</dd> <dt><code>{rules, ReadFun, WriteFun, RulesState} |

.IP
.nf
       {rules, Rules}</code></dt>

.fi

.PP
<dd>Handles storing of scanner information when parsing.</dd> <dt><code>{user_state, UserState}</code></dt> <dd>Global state variable accessible from all customization functions</dd>

.PP
<dt><code>{fetch_path, PathList}</code></dt> <dd>PathList is a list of

.IP
.nf
directories to search when fetching files. If the file in question
is not in the fetch_path, the URI will be used as a file
name.</dd>

.fi

.PP
<dt><code>{space, Flag}</code></dt> <dd><code>preserve</code> (default) to preserve spaces, <code>normalize</code> to accumulate consecutive whitespace and replace it with one space.</dd> <dt><code>{line, Line}</code></dt> <dd>To specify starting line for scanning in document which contains fragments of XML.</dd> <dt><code>{namespace_conformant, Flag}</code></dt> <dd>Controls whether to behave as a namespace conformant XML parser, <code>false</code> (default) to not otherwise <code>true</code>.</dd> <dt><code>{validation, Flag}</code></dt> <dd>Controls whether to process as a validating XML parser: <code>off</code> (default) no validation, or validation <code>dtd</code> by DTD or <code>schema</code> by XML Schema. <code>false</code> and <code>true</code> options are obsolete (i.e. they may be removed in a future release), if used <code>false</code> equals <code>off</code> and <code>true</code> equals <code>dtd</code>.</dd> <dt><code>{schemaLocation, [{Namespace,Link}|...]}</code></dt> <dd>Tells explicitly which XML Schema documents to use to validate the XML document. Used together with the <code>{validation,schema}</code> option.</dd> <dt><code>{quiet, Flag}</code></dt> <dd>Set to <code>true</code> if Xmerl should behave quietly and not output any information to standard output (default <code>false</code>).</dd> <dt><code>{doctype_DTD, DTD}</code></dt> <dd>Allows to specify DTD name when it isn't available in the XML document. This option has effect only together with <code>{validation,<code>dtd</code></code> option.</dd> <dt><code>{xmlbase, Dir}</code></dt> <dd>XML Base directory. If using string/1 default is current directory. If using file/1 default is directory of given file.</dd> <dt><code>{encoding, Enc}</code></dt> <dd>Set default character set used (default UTF-8). This character set is used only if not explicitly given by the XML declaration. </dd> <dt><code>{document, Flag}</code></dt> <dd>Set to <code>true</code> if Xmerl should return a complete XML document as an xmlDocument record (default <code>false</code>).</dd> <dt><code>{comments, Flag}</code></dt> <dd>Set to <code>false</code> if Xmerl should skip comments otherwise they will be returned as xmlComment records (default <code>true</code>).</dd> <dt><code>{default_attrs, Flag}</code></dt> <dd>Set to <code>true</code> if Xmerl should add to elements missing attributes with a defined default value (default <code>false</code>).</dd> </dl>


.RE
.B
\fBxmlElement() :: #xmlElement{}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Record \fI#xmlElement{}\fR


.RE
.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBfile_sax(Fname, CallBackModule, UserState, Options) ->\fR
\fB                  NewUserState\fR
\fB                  when\fR
\fB                      Fname :: string(),\fR
\fB                      CallBackModule :: module(),\fR
\fB                      UserState :: term(),\fR
\fB                      Options :: option_list(),\fR
\fB                      NewUserState :: term().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Parse file containing an XML document, SAX style.

.PP
Wrapper for a call to the XML parser \fIxmerl_scan\fR with a \fIhook_fun\fR for using Xmerl export functionality directly after an entity is parsed.


.RE
.B
\fBstream(Fname, Options) -> {xmlElement(), list()} | {error, Reason}\fR
\fB                when\fR
\fB                    Fname :: string(),\fR
\fB                    Options :: option_list(),\fR
\fB                    Reason :: term().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Parse file containing an XML document as a stream, DOM style.

.PP
Wrapper for a call to the XML parser \fIxmerl_scan\fR with a \fIcontinuation_fun\fR for handling streams of XML data. Note that the \fIcontinuation_fun\fR, \fIacc_fun\fR, \fIfetch_fun\fR, \fIrules\fR and \fIclose_fun\fR options cannot be user defined using this parser.


.RE
.B
\fBstream_sax(Fname, CallBackModule, UserState, Options) ->\fR
\fB                    {xmerl_scan:document(), Rest} | {error, Reason}\fR
\fB                    when\fR
\fB                        Fname :: string(),\fR
\fB                        CallBackModule :: module(),\fR
\fB                        UserState :: term(),\fR
\fB                        Options :: option_list(),\fR
\fB                        Rest :: string(),\fR
\fB                        Reason :: term().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Parse file containing an XML document as a stream, SAX style.

.PP
Wrapper for a call to the XML parser \fIxmerl_scan\fR with a \fIcontinuation_fun\fR for handling streams of XML data.  Note that the \fIcontinuation_fun\fR, \fIacc_fun\fR, \fIfetch_fun\fR, \fIrules\fR, \fIhook_fun\fR, \fIclose_fun\fR and \fIuser_state\fR options cannot be user defined using this parser.


.RE
.B
\fBstring_sax(String, CallBackModule, UserState, Options) ->\fR
\fB                    {xmerl_scan:document(), Rest} | {error, Reason}\fR
\fB                    when\fR
\fB                        String :: list(),\fR
\fB                        CallBackModule :: module(),\fR
\fB                        UserState :: term(),\fR
\fB                        Options :: option_list(),\fR
\fB                        Rest :: string(),\fR
\fB                        Reason :: term().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Parse file containing an XML document, SAX style.

.PP
Wrapper for a call to the XML parser \fIxmerl_scan\fR with a \fIhook_fun\fR for using Xmerl export functionality directly after an entity is parsed.


.RE
